name: Adult Club Membership - On Water
description: The Adult Club Membership includes the annual Rowing Canada Aviron(RCA) membership and the annual Saskatchewan Rowing Association (SRA) membership. Registered rowers are required to hold both RCA and SRA memberships for insurance purposes. The Adult Club Membership is for athletes who have completed Learn to Row and rowing experience. Schedule: Monday and Wednesday at 6-7:30 pm, Tuesday and Thursday at 5:30 am and Saturdays at 8:00 am. Fundraising Requirement: 2 Firewood ShiftsFee: $549 for May 11th-September 13th, 2025 (plus $29.40 RCA fee and $21.50 SRA fee) + $100 Fundraising Deposit

name: Adult Competitive Membership - On Water
description: The High Performance Membership includes the annual Rowing Canada Aviron(RCA) membership and the annual Saskatchewan Rowing Association (SRA) membership. Registered rowers are required to hold both RCA and SRA memberships for insurance purposes. The Adult Competitive Membership is designed for experienced rowers who plan to train daily and compete at regattas. Regular attendance and commitment to attending regattas is encouraged. Coached sessions Mondays-Fridays at 5:30 am and Saturdays at 8:00 am. Non-coached sessions available Mondays and Wednesdays at 6 pm. Fundraising Requirement - 2 Firewood delivery shiftsFee: $875 for the year (includes $29.40 RCA fee and $21.50 SRA fee) + Fundraising Deposit $100 Monthly payment option available - please select the offline payment option and to set the monthly payment up, email the club at info@reginarowing.ca.

name: Junior Novice
description: The Junior Membership includes the annual Rowing Canada Aviron(RCA) membership and the annual Saskatchewan Rowing Association (SRA) membership. _Registered rowers are required to hold both RCA and SRA memberships for insurance purposes. The Junior Novice is is our major intake programType for junior athletes(12-17yrs) with no rowing experience. The 4 sessions are used to explain the sport, teach basic body movements, boat handling, on water safety and get athletes on the water. Following the Novice sessions, athletes will be offered spots in Junior Summer Programs should they wish to continue with the sport. Dates: May 3rd, May 4th, May 10th, May 11th 10 am-1 pm.Fee: $75 (includes $29.40 RCA fee and $21.50 SRA fee)
